  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Breakfast includes a selection of fresh breads, pastries, fruit, cheeses, meats, freshly squeezed juices as well as hot options, made fresh each day using the finest local produce. </p>
<p><strong>Cibrèo Caffè </strong>is the place to head for fresh Italian coffee, lunch, aperitif or a special dinner. The outdoor seating has lovely views of the historic facades of the hotel and Palazzo Strozzi. Try the authentic Italian food and beverages on offer here – all the produce is seasonal and sustainably sourced.</p>
<p>Its open for breakfast between 7 - 11.30am, lunch from 12 -7pm and dinner from 7 - 10.30pm. The café is open to the public too.</p>
<p><strong>Bristol Winter Garden </strong>is the hotels main restaurant. It’s an amazing space covered by a historic liberty style glass ceiling, decorated with luxurious velvet seating, patterned tiles and beautiful printed wallpapers. The talented head chef has created a refined menu – the fish and fresh seafood are real specialties. The restaurant is a la carte and it is also possible to book the tasting menu.</p>
<p>Open from 7am - 10.30pm.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
