  <description><![CDATA[<p>The central location, style and character of the Helvetia &amp; Bristol can’t be matched. Here they deliver on luxury and opulence on a grand scale. It’s position between the chic fashion boutiques of Via dè Tornabuoni and the Piazza della Repubblica mean that the historic an d cultural sights of Florence, like the Duomo, the Uffizi and Ponte Vecchio, are just a short stroll away.</p>
<p>The 19<sup>th</sup> Century building has been beautifully refurbished in keeping with the old world charm of the Renaissance city; fine artworks and prints, vibrant fabrics and one of a kind antiques. But, they’ve managed to make it feel fresh and contemporary at the same time. The rooms are the same, each one is unique. They provide an ultra-comfortable space to relax, when you’re not out exploring Florence – think luxurious materials, crisp white linens and soft mattress toppers.</p>
<p>The hotels gourmet restaurant, The Winter Garden, is something special. Not only is the food delicious, but the liberty style glass roofed space has an incredible ambiance. Choose authentic Italian dishes from the a la carte menu or give the tasting menu a try. The Cibrèo Caffè has a lovely terrace that spills out onto the historic street beside – it’s one of our favourite places to go for a drink in the city, be it a coffee or a spritz.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 30 minutes by private car from Florence Airport or approx. 1 hour 20 mins by bus &amp; train or private car from Pisa Airport.</p>]]></description>
