  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Deluxe Rooms </strong>are about 19 - 32m² and sleep up to two people with a double or two single beds. The rooms are beautifully decorated with Italian oak floors, antique furniture and Murano glass chandeliers, but each is individual and very different from the next. Facilities include exclusive toiletries, bathrobes, slippers, GHD hairdryer, kettle (on request), minibar, air conditioning, TV, and a safe.</p>
<p><strong>Triple Rooms</strong> are about 28m² and sleep up to three people with double or twin beds and a single bed.</p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites </strong>are about 30 - 40m² and sleep up to 2 people with a king size bed. The rooms have a living room area as well as a sleeping area. These rooms with a view over Palazzo Strozzi and the Florentine streets are available for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Suites</strong> are about 40 - 57m² and sleep up to two people, with a king size bed. These rooms are on two levels; a living room with comfortable sofas on the lower level and a separate sleeping area on an upper level.</p>
<p><strong>Family Rooms</strong> are about 50m² and sleep up to four people. These spacious bright rooms have a mezzanine floor and a great if you’re travelling with children.</p>
<p><strong>Connecting Rooms </strong>range between 25 – 50m² and each room has a double or two single beds.</p>]]></roomsDescription>
